            desc: "Subrahmanyam Jaishankar is India's External Affairs Minister known for assertive diplomacy. In 2026, he led the BRICS Foreign Ministers meeting and various global diplomatic forums.",
            body: "<p>S. Jaishankar was born January 9, 1955, in New Delhi, son of academic K. Subrahmanyam. He had a career spanning over four decades as a diplomat, including Ambassador to the US, China, and Czech Republic, then Foreign Secretary of India 2015-2018.</p><p>After retiring, Jaishankar was appointed External Affairs Minister in May 2019 under Modi, reappointed for a second term in 2024. He's known as one of the sharpest, most outspoken diplomats globally.</p><p>Throughout 2026, Jaishankar led India's delegation at the BRICS Foreign Ministers meeting themed 'BRICS@20' and spoke at the Kultaranta Talks in Finland. He also met Iranian FM Abbas Araghchi in New Delhi.</p><p>Earlier in 2026, his blunt diplomatic style in talks with Poland's Deputy PM drew attention, a hallmark of India's confident diplomatic approach.</p>",
